<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-585-329  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 585 329.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Systems Management  Nov 1990 v41 n11 p15(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IS quality - what is it? (discussion of quality assurance ininformation systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ragozzino, Pat P.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems quality is defined as meeting IS objectivesand standards and meeting the company's goals.andP;  The best way toachieve quality is through an educational program coupled withstructured training for IS personnel.andP;  Quality assurance functionscan be implemented without quality assurance software tools.andP;  Apanel composed of information specialists concluded thatinformation systems can be improved by quality assurance and thatsenior management should be informed of the importance of qualityassurance.andP;  The panel also concluded that people working withquality assurance should develop their careers formally so thatthe information systems environment will recognize the importanceof quality assurance functions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information SystemsQuality ControlPlanning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>